<subSubSection id="C3056522FFA2FFD8E696FA3D8AEBF8CE" pageId="7" pageNumber="180" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA036A9FFA2FFD8E696FA3D8AEBF8CE" blockId="7.[151,1437,1446,1869]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis id="B96BEABBFFA2FFD8E696FA3D8F18F9C3" bold="true" box="[199,322,1518,1544]" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C1F4D2AFFA2FFD8E719FA3C8C52F9C2" authorityName="Tolkanitz" authorityYear="1993" box="[328,520,1519,1545]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Exochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="180" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hirsutus">
<emphasis id="B96BEABBFFA2FFD8E719FA3C8C52F9C2" box="[328,520,1519,1545]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">Exochus hirsutus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by the combination of the following characters: face not strongly swollen, black in lower half and yellow in upper half; clypeus laterally and malar space yellow; frons black with short yellow lines along eye orbits (reaching only the level of the antennla sockets); yellow marks opposite to lateral ocelli not elongated; clypeus with apical margin straight; occipital carina absent dorsally; meso- and metasoma black except upper hind corner of pronotum and subtegular ridge yellow; propodeum with area superomedia closed apically, costulae absent, area dentipara densely pubescent; fore wing with vein 
<emphasis id="B96BEABBFFA2FFD8E277F9708A02F977" box="[1062,1112,1699,1724]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">cu-a</emphasis>
strongly distad of 
<emphasis id="B96BEABBFFA2FFD8E37EF9708B22F976" box="[1327,1400,1699,1725]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="180">Rs&amp;M</emphasis>
by about 0.4 of own length; third laterotergite straight from the proximal end, wedge-shaped; legs generally yellowishorange, coxae with black marks, hind femora apically, hind tibia basally and apically fuscous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
